<section>
	<h2>Inclass work</h2>
	<p>As a user, I want my smartphone to display contextual information from the physical world.</p>
	<p>As a dev, generate a QR code linking to our school's web address, so the smartphone browser will open said web page. The QR Code should be embedded into a web page.</p>
	<h3>Technologies</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Google Infographic API</li>
		<li>Smartphone with QR code scanning app</li>
		<li>HTML</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Inclass work</h2>
	<p>As a user, I want my vitals stored in a MeCard format.</p>
	<p>As a dev, collect first &amp; last name, job title, and web address via an HTML form.  On submit display the captured data in a MeCard format.</p>

	<h3>Technologies</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>JavaScript</li>
		<li>jQuery</li>
		<li>HTML</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Inclass work</h2>
	<p>As a dev, collect first &amp; last name, job title, and web address via an HTML form then generate a QR code containing meCard data.  When the QR code is scanned, the mobile phone user will have the option of adding to their address book.</p>

	<h3>Technologies</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Google Infographic API</li>
		<li>meCard</li>
		<li>Smartphone with QR code scanning app</li>
		<li>JavaScript</li>
	</ul>
</section>
